      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 7.98,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 7.98,
      "end": 19.1,
      "text": "information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org. Recorded by Annie Coleman in St. Louis, Missouri",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 19.1,
      "end": 23.38,
      "text": "on January 13, 2006.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 25.1,
      "end": 26.34,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 28.18,
      "end": 30.66,
      "text": "The Ass, the Fox, and the Lion.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 32.28,
      "end": 36.6,
      "text": "An Ass and a Fox went into partnership and",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 36.6,
      "end": 43.12,
      "text": "salad out to forage for food together. They hadn't gone far before they saw a lion coming",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 43.12,
      "end": 49.74,
      "text": "their way, at which they were both dreadfully frightened. But the Fox thought he saw a way",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 49.74,
      "end": 55.48,
      "text": "of saving his own skin, and went boldly up to the lion, and whispered in his ear,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 56.36,
      "end": 61.78,
      "text": "all managed that you shall get hold of the Ass without the trouble of stalking him, if",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 61.78,
      "end": 63.44,
      "text": "you'll promise to let me go free.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 64.54,
      "end": 72.54,
      "text": "The Lion agreed to this, and the Fox then rejoined his companion, and contrived before long to",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 72.54,
      "end": 78.78,
      "text": "lead him by a hidden pit, which some hunter had dug as a trap for wild animals, and into",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 78.78,
      "end": 86.56,
      "text": "which he fell. When the Lion saw that the Ass was safely caught and couldn't get away, it",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 86.56,
      "end": 93.48,
      "text": "was to the Fox that he first turned his attention, and he soon finished him off, and then, at his",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 93.48,
      "end": 96.42,
      "text": "leisure, proceeded to feast upon the Ass.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 97.76,
      "end": 102.58,
      "text": "Betray a friend, and you'll often find you have ruined yourself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 104.5,
      "end": 108.52,
      "text": "End of the Ass, the Fox, and the Lion.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
